{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Place flour, yeast, olive oil, water and salt in mixing bowl then knead <nobr>40 sec\/<\/nobr>.","Transfer dough to a lightly-oiled bowl and leave to rise until doubled in size (at least 1 hour). Clean mixing bowl.","Tip dough out onto a work surface and shape into a large ball using lightly-floured hands.","Roll dough into a rectangle and divide into 8 equal pieces.","Shape each piece into a smooth ball using lightly-floured hands. Cover with a tea towel and set aside to rest while making filling."]},{"title":"Lamb Filling","content":["Place onions and garlic in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add oil then cook <nobr>5 min\/120°C\/speed <\/nobr>. Remove lid and leave to cool for 5-10 minutes.","Add lamb, pine nuts, cinnamon, salt and pepper then mix <nobr>20 sec\/\/speed <\/nobr>."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["Preheat oven to 200°C and line a large baking tray with baking paper.","With lightly-floured hands and working with one ball at a time, roll out to form a long oval. Roll across the middle to make it slightly wider without losing the oval shape (approx. 23 cm x 13 cm). Repeat with remaining balls of dough.","Place lamb filling down the centre of each oval of dough flattening it out a little, leaving 3-4 cm at each end.","Fold long edges in, leaving 4 cm uncovered in the centre.","Pinch each short end together and twist into a small ball to resemble a small boat.","Transfer pides to prepared baking tray. Moisten dough edges with water and scatter with sesame seeds. Leave to rest for 30 minutes.","Spoon 2 tsp yoghurt on top of each pide then bake 15-20 minutes (200°C) until puffed and golden.","Remove from oven, brush with extra virgin olive oil and sprinkle with sumac and coriander leaves before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["500 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","15 g dried instant yeast","320 g water, warm","1 tsp fine sea salt","30 g olive oil"]},{"title":"Lamb Filling","content":["80 g onions, quartered","1 garlic clove","20 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for brushing and greasing","500 g lamb mince, broken in pieces","50 g toasted pine nuts","1 tsp ground cinnamon","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["100 g water","4 tsp sesame seeds","250 g natural yoghurt","1 Tbsp sumac","½ bunch fresh coriander, leaves only"]}],"id":"r248416","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-R2wNL65OeNg\/XZQGnlhNUeI\/AAAAAAAAb_8\/MWWcH_iydAAweLJV5fEPKpiEPIdsu3JMgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Uo9pZxNvInNNVUha.png","title":"Pide with Lamb, Cinnamon, Pine Nuts and Yoghurt","publishedAt":"2018-03-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"20 g","fat":"28 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"54 g","calories":"2293 kJ \/ 548 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and baking paper, rolling pin, pastry brush, oven","hintsAndTricks":["When preparing the dough, at the end of <nobr>step 5<\/nobr> the balls of dough can be covered and refrigerated or frozen for later use.","Depending on the size of your oven you may need two trays with <nobr>4 pides<\/nobr> on each.","For a vegetarian option, replace the lamb mince with a similar weight of cooked spinach mixed with ricotta."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","2h 15m","8 portions"]}